                <h5>About Visulate CMBS</h5>
                <p>This application is a proof of concept demo that explores the potential for using AI to analyze Commercial Mortgage-Backed Securities (CMBS) data. You can use it to explore property-level details for loans that collateralize a CMBS trust. </p>

                <p>CMBS are a type of asset-backed security that pools together mortgages on commercial properties, such as office buildings, shopping centers, and hotels. Investors in CMBS receive regular payments based on the cash flows generated by the underlying mortgages. CMBS data is reported to the SEC under Regulation AB II, which requires issuers to provide detailed information about the underlying assets in a standardized format. This data is submitted using SEC Form <a href="/cmbs/ABS-EE">ABS-EE</a>. Issuing entities also submit deal-specific information using a <a href="/cmbs/FWP">FWP</a>.</p>
                <p>Visulate CMBS is designed to help you explore this data in a user-friendly way. It provides AI generated summaries for each CMBS offering based on its original term sheet filed with the SEC. It also provides AI generated analysis of the underlying assets, including property details, location maps, and insights into the performance of the properties based on the most recent EX-102 ABS-EE filing. The AI analysis is powered by Google's Gemini model, which can provide detailed answers to questions about the CMBS offerings and their underlying assets.</p>
                <p>To get started, select a CMBS offering from the dropdown list at the top of the page. Once selected, you can view a summary of the offering and its property details then ask follow-up questions about the offering and its underlying assets.</p>

                <p>If you have any questions or feedback, please contact <a href="mailto:support@visulate.com">support@visulate.com</a> or contact Susan Goldthorp on (321) 698 5198</p>

